// Setting common testing on startup
str_checkbox_testing_startup_title=ًں§ھ Test at startup
str_checkbox_testing_startup_description=ًں§ھ Automatically test site availability when the application starts.
When enabled, Unblock will immediately check whether bypasses for major services (YouTube, Discord, Instagram, etc.) are working.
Test results will be shown on the main screen as a list of accessible domains.
This helps quickly verify that the selected configuration is working and, if needed, rerun automatic configuration selection.

// Setting common enable dns hosts
str_checkbox_enable_dns_hosts_title=ًں“پ Local DNS (hosts)
str_checkbox_enable_dns_hosts_description=ًں“پ Use system hosts file to bypass DNS blocks.
When enabled, Unblock adds domain-to-IP mappings to the hosts file (C:\Windows\System32\drivers\etc\hosts), bypassing your ISP's DNS servers.
This allows blocking circumvention at the DNS level without additional software.
The hosts file is checked first on any network request, so the redirection happens before any external DNS lookup.
Safe: when disabled, Unblock restores the original hosts file content.

// Setting common enable local proxy telegram
str_checkbox_enable_proxy_tg_title=ًں“± Proxy for Telegram
str_checkbox_enable_proxy_tg_description=ًں”’ Local proxy for Telegram
Creates a proxy server on your device. It does not connect to external servers and works locally to bypass blocks.
str_button_proxy_link_tg_title=ًں”— Connect proxy to Telegram

// Setting checkbox zapret winws enable
str_unblock_enable_title=ًں”“ Enable Zapret2 (winws2)
str_unblock_enable_description=Primary bypass mode based on the Zapret2 DPI evader (winws2).
Analyzes and modifies network packets in real time, altering TLS handshake parameters (ClientHello) and other signatures.
Bypasses most types of blocking without redirecting traffic to external servers.
Works locally and requires no additional proxies.

